.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
An estimation of the non\-coherent, weighted tail mean
\&\s-2\u[1]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[2]\d\s+2 [$\widehat{NCTM}_{n,\alpha}(X)$]
is given by the weighted mean of the
.PP
\fBEquation 1.24. \fR \&\s-2\u[3]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[4]\d\s+2 \e[ \elambda = \einf\eleft\e{ l \eleft| \efrac{1}{\ebar{w}_n}\esum_{i=1}^{l} w_i \egeq \ealpha \eright\&. \eright\e} \e] .RE
.PP
smallest samples (left tail) or the weighted mean of the
.PP
\fBEquation 1.25. \fR \&\s-2\u[5]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[6]\d\s+2 \e[ n + 1 \- \erho = n + 1 \- \esup\eleft\e{ r \eleft| \efrac{1}{\ebar{w}_n}\esum_{i=r}^{n} w_i \egeq (1 \- \ealpha) \eright\&. \eright\e} \e] .RE
.PP
largest samples (right tail) above a quantile
\&\s-2\u[7]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[8]\d\s+2 [$\hat{q}_{\alpha}$]
of level
\&\s-2\u[9]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[10]\d\s+2 [$\alpha$],
\&\s-2\u[11]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[12]\d\s+2 [$n$]
being the total number of sample and
\&\s-2\u[13]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[14]\d\s+2 [$\bar{w}_n$]
the sum of all
\&\s-2\u[15]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[12]\d\s+2 [$n$]
weights:
.PP
\fBEquation 1.26. \fR \&\s-2\u[16]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[17]\d\s+2 \e[ \ewidehat{NCTM}_{n,\ealpha}^{\emathrm{left}}(X) = \efrac{\esum_{i=1}^{\elambda} w_i X_{i:n}}{\esum_{i=1}^{\elambda} w_i}, \e] .RE
.PP
\fBEquation 1.27. \fR \&\s-2\u[18]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[19]\d\s+2 \e[ \ewidehat{NCTM}_{n,\ealpha}^{\emathrm{right}}(X) = \efrac{\esum_{i=\erho}^n w_i X_{i:n}}{\esum_{i=\erho}^n w_i}\&. \e] .RE
.PP

